p.strong: After EVERY IRQ handler, you MUST send EOI or the PIC freezes that IRQ line forever.

div.p: For IRQ0-7 (master only): outb(0x20, 0x20) For IRQ8-15 (slave + master): outb(0xA0, 0x20) then outb(0x20, 0x20)
Spurious IRQ7: do NOT send EOI (PIC's ISR bit was never set) Spurious IRQ15: send EOI to master only (slave did not set ISR)

g.text: IRQ2 (Cascde) CPU vec 10 SEG NOT PRES!

div.p: Mask byte written to 0x21 (DATA) 0xFC = 1111 1100b bit0=0 IRQ0 ENABLED (timer) bit1=0 IRQ1 ENABLED (keyboard) bit2=1 IRQ2 masked (cascade handles it) bit3..7=1 IRQ3-7 masked

g.text: bit4 = 1 MUST BE 1: signals ICW1 (vs OCW)
bits2..0 = 000 ignored (auto-filled by PIC with IRQ#)
BITMASK: bit2=1 means IRQ line 2 has a slave
Hardware: slave INT output wired to master IRQ2 input
NUMERIC ID: slave identity = 2 (matches master bit2)
Used by master to know which slave to cascade to
bit1 = 0 normal EOI (manual; AEOI=1 is auto but risky)
8259A PIC requires ~1s to process each ICW write
Modern CPUs execute OUT in ~10ns 100 too fast!
Without delay: PIC misses ICW bytes stuck in wrong state
